org.hazelwire.gui
Class Challenge

java.lang.Object
  org.hazelwire.gui.Challenge

public class Challenge
extends java.lang.Object

Instances of this class represent a challenge, which is a part of a Mod that represents a Flag and the values associated with it.

Constructor Detail

Challenge

public Challenge(int id,
                 java.lang.String description,
                 int points)
Creates an instance of Challenge by specifying its id, its description and its value.

Parameters:
id - unique integer that is used to tell different challenges apart.
description - String that describes the Challenge
points - integer number that indicates the value of the Flag associated with this challenge. The default amount of points for this Challenge is set to be the value of points.

Challenge

public Challenge(int id)
Creates an 'empty' Challenge. This method is only used for comparisons, since two challenges are equal whenever their id is equal. This method therefore sets only the id and assigns standard values to the other variables.

Parameters:
id - unique integer that is used to tell different challenges apart.

setPoints

public void setPoints(int points)
Using this method, the value of the Flag may be increased or decreased. Using this method does not change the default amount of points this Challenge is worth.

Parameters:
points - the integer amount of points that should be the new value of the Challenge.

toFlag

public Flag toFlag()
Creates a new Flag with the data that is stored in this instance of Challenge: points, id and description.

Returns:
The new Flag.

equals

public boolean equals(java.lang.Object o)
This method overrides the standard equals method, in order to be able to search a Collection of Challenges. It checks whether both Objects are instances of Challenge and if that is the case, it compares their ids.

Overrides:
equals in class java.lang.Object
Parameters:
o - Object that is compared to this Challenge.
